The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Blair Iran sanctions 

 London, Feb. 7 (Reuters): A potential rise in oil prices should not stop the international community from imposing sanctions on Iran if it believes they are needed, Britains Tony Blair said today. 

 Obviously they (Iran) have a certain position within the energy market but that should not deter us from taking action if thats where we get to, Blair said. 

 Smoking 

 London (Reuters): Scientists called for an overhaul of how toxins in cigarette smoke are measured after industry documents showed how they can be used to deceive smokers. 

 China editor 

 Beijing (Reuters): A Chinese editor has died from injuries after traffic police beat him up for an expose about exorbitant bicycle licence fees. 




